# dorv — core rules

Full agent playbook: [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md). Backlog order: [docs/PRIORITIES.md](../../docs/PRIORITIES.md).

## Principles

- Simplicity over architectural beauty; smallest change that satisfies the Linear issue.
- TDD first; ~100% coverage on touched code; CI gates merges.
- Monorepo: one README per package; root README links to them.
- prek for pre-commit — do not skip hooks unless the user asks.

## v0.1.0 boundaries

- **In scope:** DirectAdapter (PAT + `chrome.identity`), 2-min poll, `chrome.storage.local`.
- **Out of scope unless assigned:** backend, webhooks, GitHub App, auto-updating doc on new commits, non-MD sync, multiple docs per PR.

## Agent behavior

- Prefer one Linear issue per task; follow dependency order in PRIORITIES.md.
- No commits/PRs unless the user explicitly requests.
- No secrets in repo; use `.env.example` placeholders.
- Prevent double-sync (`hasByGH` / `hasByDoc`, `source` on mappings). Isolate errors per PR in sync loops.
